Proposed law modifies present law by specifying that operations of a personal delivery
device is treated the same as a pedestrian or bicyclist.
Present law provides specifications for operation of the devices relative to traffic and
compliance with regulations.
Proposed law retains the specifications of present law but adds provisions for operation
within a pedestrian or nonpedestrian area.
Present law allows for local prohibitions of personal delivery devices in the interest of public
safety.
Proposed law changes the provision from a prohibition against to the regulation of personal
delivery devices in the interest of public safety provided the regulations are not inconsistent
with present law.
